{"title_page": "Andrea Bertin", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Andrea Bertin\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1992|2|27|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Carate Brianza]], Italy\n| height = \n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| currentclub = [[Mantova F.C.|Mantova]]\n| youthyears1 = 2004\u20132009\n| youthclubs1 = [[F.C. Internazionale Milano|Internazionale]]\n| youthyears2 = 2009\u20132010\n| youthclubs2 = [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]]\n| years1 = 2010\u20132011\n| caps1 = 11\n| goals1 = \n| clubs1 = [[Aurora Pro Patria 1919|Pro Patria]]\n| years2 = 2011\u20132013\n| caps2 = 58\n| goals2 = \n| clubs2 = [[Mantova F.C.|Mantova]]\n| totalcaps = \n| totalgoals = \n| club-update = \n}}\n'''Andrea Bertin''' (born 27 February 1992) is a former [[Football in Italy|Italian footballer]] who played as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Youth career===\nBorn in [[Carate Brianza]], the [[Province of Monza and Brianza]] (historically in the [[Province of Milan]]), Bertin, also known as Bertinelli, started his career at [[F.C. Internazionale Milano|Internazionale]]. He played for its ''Giovanissimi Regionali B'' under-14 team in 2004\u201305 season to ''Allievi Nazionali'' under-17 team in 2008\u201309 season. Bertin finished as the runner-up of ''Allievi Nazionali'' League in June 2009 as starting right-back.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.inter.it/aas/news/reader?N=31636&L=en|title=Under-17s defeated: thanks all the same |date=19 June 2009|accessdate=17 March 2012|work=www.inter.it|publisher=FC Internazionale Milano}}</ref> Bertin also played as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] in [[Formation (association football)#3\u20135\u20132|3\u20135\u20132 formation]] for ''Allievi''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.inter.it/aas/news/reader?N=31571&L=en|title=Under-17s reach championship playoffs |date=7 June 2009|accessdate=17 March 2012|work=www.inter.it|publisher=FC Internazionale Milano}}</ref> and also played once for ''Primavera''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.inter.it/aas/news/reader?N=31161&L=en|title=Primavera: Treviso 0-2 Inter |date=4 April 2009|accessdate=17 March 2012|work=www.inter.it|publisher=FC Internazionale Milano}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 August 2009, Bertin moved to fellow [[Serie A]] club [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]] in temporary deal, re-joining former teammate [[Nestor Djengoue]] and Daniele Co.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.inter.it/aas/news/reader?N=32083&L=en|title=Loan moves for three |date=31 August 2009|accessdate=17 March 2012|work=www.inter.it|publisher=FC Internazionale Milano}}</ref> That season Inter did not had its [[Campionato Nazionale Dante Berretti|Berretti under-18 team]] in its youth rank and no room for Bertin in Primavera, as the club already promoted [[Felice Natalino]] and [[Cristiano Biraghi]] from ''Allievi'' as well as had senior member likes [[Giulio Donati]] and [[Davide Santon]]. Bertin was a member of Chievo's [[Campionato Nazionale Primavera|Primavera under-20 team]], as a starting defender along with Djengoue.\n\nHe started his consulting career at KPMG Advisory in 2017. Never played soccer after that.\n\n===Lega Pro clubs===\nOn 12 August 2010 Bertin was signed by Chievo on free transfer,<ref name=Chievo2011bilancio>AC Chievo-Verona s.r.l. Report and Accounts on 30 June 2011 {{in lang|it}}</ref> after Inter signed another fullback [[Davide Faraoni]], but Bertin was immediately left for [[Aurora Pro Patria 1919|Pro Patria]] in [[co-ownership (football)|co-ownership deal]] for a peppercorn fee of \u20ac500, rejoining teammate [[Amedeo Benedetti (footballer)|Amedeo Benedetti]].<ref name=Chievo2011bilancio/> In June 2011 both clubs failed to agree the price of the remain 50% registration rights before the deadline. On 24 June both clubs submitted their bid to [[Lega Serie A]] in a sealed envelope. On 25 June the League committee announced that Chievo bought back Bertin for \u20ac1,000<ref name=Chievo2011bilancio/>\n\nBertin was immediately left for [[Mantova F.C.|Mantova]] along with [[Andrea Burato]], also in [[Lega Pro Seconda Divisione]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/?action=read&id=277636|title=Mantova, dal Chievo in arrivo Bertin e Burato|date=28 June 2011|accessdate=17 March 2012|publisher=Tutto Mercato Web|language=Italian}}</ref> Bertin was the starting right-back (wing-back) of the team in 4\u20134\u20132 formation or 3\u20135\u20132 formation, ahead [[Pellegrino Albanese]], former Inter teammate and [[Sebastiano Girelli]], experienced [[Mantua|Mantovani]]. Bertin also selected to the representative team of the second division group B, for 2012 [[Lega Pro Quadrangular Tournament]]. Bertin was the starting defender of the team, and finished as the fourth.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lega-pro.com/sito/index.php/rappresentativa-news/312-tabellino-gara-2-quadrangolare-|title=TABELLINO GARA 2 QUADRANGOLARE |date=24 January 2012|accessdate=22 June 2012|publisher=Lega Pro|language=Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lega-pro.com/sito/index.php/rappresentativa-news/313-finale-terzo-e-quarto-posto-quadrangolare-lega-pro-|title=FINALE TERZO E QUARTO POSTO QUADRANGOLARE LEGA PRO |date=26 January 2012|accessdate=22 June 2012|publisher=Lega Pro|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://aic.football.it/scheda/23228/bertin-andrea.htm Football.it Profile] {{in lang|it}}\n\n{{use dmy dates|date=March 2012}}\n\n{{portal bar|Association football|Italy}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bertin, Andrea}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Carate Brianza]]\n[[Category:Italian footballers]]\n[[Category:Inter Milan players]]\n[[Category:A.C. ChievoVerona players]]\n[[Category:Aurora Pro Patria 1919 players]]\n[[Category:Mantova 1911 S.S.D. players]]\n[[Category:Association football fullbacks]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name              