\n| registration_plate = [[Vehicle registration plates of Austria|LA]]\n| postal_code_type   = [[List of postal codes in Austria|Postal code]]\n| postal_code        = 6561\n| area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Austria|Area code]]\n| area_code      = 05444\n| website   = [http://www.ischgl.tirol.gv.at www.ischgl.tirol.gv.at]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''Ischgl''' ({{convert|1377|m|disp=or||}}) is a town in the [[Paznaun]] valley in the [[Austria]]n state of [[state of Tyrol|Tyrol]]. Its [[ski resort]] ''Silvretta Arena Ischgl-Samnaun'' is connected with the ski resort of [[Samnaun]] across the border in [[Switzerland]] to form one of the largest skiing resorts in the [[Alps]]. Ischgl was a major hotspot of the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe]].\n\n==Ski resort==\nIschgl is located on the Austrian side of one of the world's largest ski areas. Its {{convert|238|km|||}} of groomed pistes are served by over 45 mechanical lifts including [[Aerial tramway|cable cars]], [[Gondola lift|gondolas]], [[Detachable chairlift|detachable chair lifts]] and some [[T-bar lift|T-bars]]. Three ropeways give access to the ski area from the village: the Pardatschgratbahn, the Fimbabahn & the Silvrettabahn. Only the Fimbabahn and the Silvrettabahn have middle stations.<ref name=\"ischgl.com\">[http://www.ischgl.com/ Ischgl.com]</ref> Many of the lifts converge at Idalp, where there is a restaurant. The area above Idalp offers wide, easy pistes and a snow park. Other parts of the Ischgl area, towards H\u00f6llboden and Paznauner Thaya, offer many red runs and some more challenging blacks. The steepest run in the resort is a black run with a gradient of 70%, located in the H\u00f6llboden bowl, and accessed by the \"Lange Wand\" chair lift. Paznauner Thaya offers many red runs suitable for intermediate-level skiers.\n\nIschgl is known for lively [[apr\u00e8s-ski]] parties and nightlife. The resort hosts pop concerts celebrating the end of the annual ski season (''Top of the Mountain Concert'') at the Idalp ({{convert|2300|m|disp=or||}}). [[Bob Dylan]], [[Tina Turner]], [[Elton John]], [[Mariah Carey]], [[The Corrs]], [[Thirty Seconds to Mars]], [[Rod Stewart]], [[Jon Bon Jovi]], [[Nena]], [[Sugababes]], [[Enrique Iglesias]], [[Pink (singer)|Pink]], [[Anastacia]], [[Beyonc\u00e9 Knowles|Beyonc\u00e9]], [[Melanie C]], [[Rihanna]], [[Gabriella Cilmi]], [[Leona Lewis]], [[Kylie Minogue]], [[Katy Perry]] and [[Alicia Keys]] have performed at these concerts. In April 2002 [[Bill Clinton]] gave a speech at Ischgl.\n\n==Coronavirus pandemic hotspot==\nIschgl was identified as a major hotspot of the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe]]. Hundreds of [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Germany|infections in Germany]] and the [[Nordic countries]] were traced back to the ski resort [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iceland|starting from Iceland]] on 1 March with transmissions occurring from late February on. Significant portion of the cases were further traced to ''Kitzloch'' [[apr\u00e8s-ski]] bar at the resort, where sharing of [[whistle]]s were likely conduits of contagion. Even as health authorities in other countries began raising warnings against travel to Ischgl, the resort remained open with Tyrolean authorities playing down the risks.<ref name=grull2020-03-20>{{cite web |last1=Gr\u00fcll |first1=Philipp |title=How an Austrian ski paradise became a COVID-19 hotspot |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/news/ischgl-oesterreichisches-skiparadies-als-corona-hotspot/ |website=www.euractiv.com |publisher=[[Euractiv]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323174922/https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/news/ischgl-oesterreichisches-skiparadies-als-corona-hotspot/ |archivedate=23 March 2020 |language=en |date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> The bar was eventually closed on 10 March and the whole town quarantined from 13 March on.<ref name=mayr>{{cite news |last1=Mayr |first1=Walter |title=Austrian Ski Resort Flings Coronavirus Around Europe |url=https://www.spiegel.de/international/europe/ischgl-austrian-ski-resort-flings-coronavirus-around-europe-a-68e10295-1d9c-42cc-9e52-7fea35436479 |accessdate=20 March 2020 |work=Der Spiegel |date=17 March 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200321131420/https://www.spiegel.de/international/europe/ischgl-austrian-ski-resort-flings-coronavirus-around-europe-a-68e10295-1d9c-42cc-9e52-7fea35436479 |archivedate=21 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Karnitschnig>{{cite web |last1=Karnitschnig |first1=Matthew |title=The Austrian ski town that spread coronavirus across the Continent |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/the-austrian-ski-town-that-spread-coronavirus-across-the-continent/ |website=Politico |accessdate=21 March 2020 |date=19 March 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200323121016/https://www.politico.eu/article/the-austrian-ski-town-that-spread-coronavirus-across-the-continent/ |archivedate=23 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery class=\"left\">\nFile:Ischgl, katholische Pfarrkirche heilige Nikolaus Dm64328 foto4 2014-07-23 15.00.jpg|Roman Catholic church St. Nikolaus\nFile:Tussen Ischgl en Kappl, rivier de Ischgl foto6 2014-07-23 14.52.jpg|Trisanna river\n</gallery>\n{{wide image|Panorama Ischgl Pardorama.jpg|1000px|Panorama of Ischgl Pardorama}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikivoyage}}\n*[http://www.ischgl.com/ Official Ischgl website]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20120224175134/http://www.360travelguide.com/360VirtualTour.asp?iCode=isc12 Panoramic photo of Ischgl resort centre]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{commons category}}\n{{Cities and towns in Landeck (district)}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Ski areas and resorts in Austria]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Tyrol (state)]]\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Landeck District]]\n[[Category:Verwall Alps]]\n[[Category:Silvretta Alps]]\n", "name_user": "Volt4ire", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSki resort:added c